Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways and
thinly slice. Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Pour the @water{750%ml} into a #saucepan{}. Add the @vegetable stock powder{2}, then
bring to the boil and stir to dissolve. Lower the heat. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of
@oil in a #large saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
@British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and cook until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the
mushrooms and leek to the bacon and stir-fry until softened, another
~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @Arborio rice{175%g} to the pan and cook over medium-low heat for
~{3%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, stir together and
allow it to evaporate. Bring another saucepan of water to the boil for the mangetout.

Stir a ladle of hot stock into the rice. When the stock has been absorbed by the
rice, stir in another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue
stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time. The cooking time should take
~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked
through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

When the risotto has 5 mins left, add the @mangetout{150%g} to the to the pan of
boiling water along with @salt{0.25%tsp}. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes}, until just
tender, then drain in a #colander{}.

Once cooked, remove the risotto from the heat. Stir in the @unsalted butter{30%g},
half the parsley and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}
along with the mangetout. Season to taste with @salt and @ground black pepper.
Serve your risotto in deep #bowls{} with the rest of the hard Italian cheese and
parsley scattered on top. Enjoy!